               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400302-name-400" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-400" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-400" type="surname" value="BRUNT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-400" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BRUNT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. About eight o'clock on the 28th of February, I and another officer were at Leighton, in Essex—I saw the prisoner pass me with something bulky in his pocket—I asked what he had got—he said, what was that to me—I desired the other officer to search him, and he found this bridle in his pocket—(<hi rend="italic">producing it</hi>)—he said he bought it of a man for 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I found the owner, Mr. West, of Church-street, Hackney.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400302-name-401" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-401" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
